INSERT INTO `email` VALUES (549, 1, NULL, 727, NULL, NULL, 'Mail From:  WiggleWorm\nDate:  Friday 30-Sep-2005 08:01 CDT\nHi Jim.\nI don''t get the "Terminate Disk and\nMigate user Name" I would guess it will\njust move a name from one disk to\nanother. But then I don''t get why\nyou would have to type in the name\nof the other disk. Is the name of the\nother disk have to be a name that you\nwant the name you are using now to\ncopy over?\nI got this WiggleWorm on another disk\nand Leonette, Katydid, Katydidnt on\nanother disk. So how would I move\nthe WiggleWorm on to the other disk?\nIs there a way to just delete the\nWiggleWorm account then can make a new\nname on the other was WiggleWorm?\nI think you need better text in the\n"Terminate Disk and Migate user Name" I\nread it over and over and I am not sure\nhow to do it right.\nI do get now that you have to back out\nto the menu for it to update your disk.\n-Raymond Day\n', 'N', '2005-09-30 08:06:44');
INSERT INTO `email` VALUES (550, 727, NULL, 1, NULL, NULL, 'Mail From:  QADMIN jim\nDate:  Friday 30-Sep-2005 09:23 CDT\nTo move WiggleWorm to the other disk,\nboot with the WW disk, go to Terminate\nmenu item, and type in Leonette\nThat will close out the WW disk and move\nthe WW acct to the Leonette disk\nThen, boot the Leonette disk\nInitially, it will not show the WW\naccount.  Boot using another account\nand then go to a menu (any menu)\nIt will say it is updating the disk\nand it will install WiggleWorm on\nthe Leonette disk\nThen, go to change names item and\nWiggleWorm will show up.\n.\nThe text was the best I could do\nin the space I have.  Later, I will\ncreate a FAQ for it, but you must\nrealize this was mainly just for\na one time deal (so folks who created)\nmultiple names on multiple disks\ncould move them to one disk.\nAs well, Ray, there is just not enough\ntime to get everything documented\nproperly right now.\nWhen in doubt, don''t use the\nmenu items, as I won''t have time to\ndocument them well for a while\n.\nFor example, in this email, you want\nbetter docs on this menu item\nBut in the chat, you want to know if I a\nam working on SuperQ.  I can only do\nso much, so you need to decide what\nit is you would most want me to work on\nand only ask me about that.  I can\nonly work on one thing at a time.\n.\nJim\n', 'N', '2005-09-30 09:27:57');
