INSERT INTO `email` VALUES (576, 6, NULL, 637, NULL, NULL, 'Mail From:  GeoRep RP\nDate:  Saturday 1-Oct-2005 21:56 CDT\nHello, Jeff... Well, first of all, Jim\nalluded to the fact that my "idea" isn''t\nentirely original... you guys have\nprobably been thinking along these lines\n... although I wonder if this focused...\nanyway, I hope this is useful\nsomehow...\nI was thinking...\nWhat would net the new Q-Link thousands\nof new members... if not tens of\nthousands...\nHere''s my thinking...\n1) The "retro computing" and "retro\ngaming" scenes are huge... there are\neven magazines devoted to that...\nI picked up a UK slick magazine at\nBarnes and Noble last week on the topic\n2) The emulation scene continues to grow\n3) There is no "online service" for\nthose interest areas...\n4) Q-Link matches the flavor of those\nscenes thematically in a very artful and\nappealing way!\n5) Resurrecting the old Q-Link forums\nis a GREAT thing and will appeal to the\nold Q users like me\n6) But you can reach a much larger\naudience by also incorporating NEW\nforums...\nlike...\nThe Retro Gamer Forum\nCommodore Emulation Forum\nApple 2 Emulation Forum\nAtari 8-Bit Emulation Forum\nOld School Applications\netc.\nYou''ll get written up in even the\nmainstream publications (think\nPC Magazine, etc.) because you will be\nserving a contemporary purpose AS WELL\nAS the nostalgic one for those of us who\nwere actually there way back when.\n7) I definitely love the idea of\n', 'N', '2005-10-01 22:04:32');
INSERT INTO `email` VALUES (577, 6, NULL, 637, NULL, NULL, 'Mail From:  GeoRep RP\nDate:  Saturday 1-Oct-2005 22:05 CDT\n7) I definitely love the idea of\npopulating the News areas with RSS\ncontent, etc.\nbut consider that the "authentic"\nwindow dressing that makes this place\nso cool... Of course people who really\nwant the news will still go to CNN.com\n... Still as many of those features that\ncan be resurrected... especially\nautomatically without any human upkeep\nwill add so much...\n8) Still, you can attract MANY community\nleaders interested in these new retro\nforums... while you may have trouble\nresurrecting things like the old\nCooking Club or the Auto Club or the\nWriters Nook, etc. since there are\nother more contemporary outlets for\nactual interests like that. The retro\ncomputing people, on the other hand,\nmay PREFER this interface to the web\nsince it is so incredibly cool, fits\nthe topic so well, and encourages\ncommunity.\nWell, that''s it.\nHope this proves useful at some point.\nIt provides a focused niche.\nBest regards.\nRandy\nGeoRep RP\n', 'N', '2005-10-01 22:09:10');
INSERT INTO `email` VALUES (578, 637, NULL, 6, NULL, NULL, 'Mail From:  QGUIDE ob\nDate:  Saturday 1-Oct-2005 22:15 CDT\nI hadn''t considered the entire retro\ncommunity, although I would not\nhesitate to include them.  The original\ntelbbs site was hosted at petscii.com\nand later moved to a more generic name\nto include other computer types,\nhowever, the CBM community is the only\ncommunity that is moving into new tech\nnology quickly.  Qlink is an example of\nthis.   I am very open to new forums\noutside the existing Qlink ones.\nLike most things, I find myself ahead of\nthe curve when it comes to my hobbies.\nI suspect that within a year or so there\nwill be a huge move to retro computing.\nIts nice to already be here. :)\nJeff\n', 'N', '2005-10-01 22:21:47');
