INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES (66, 476, 0, 409, 'Hangman 1701.bas', 'METAL MAGE', '2005-09-14 10:22:01', 0, 'SUBJ: Hangman 1701.bas                 FROM: METAL MAGE  09/14/2005 S# 476\nI have been studying the listing that Jeff Stone posted for Hangman.  It is in BASIC and he figured out a way to list the code, after making some changes to list it correctly.\n\nHas anyone looked at this yet?\n\nHere is what I think it does:\n\nline 360 is the main input loop which ends at line 500 to repeat using a goto\n\na$ is the key pressed on the keyboard\nmg$ is the text string to display\nn1$ is the name of the player\nn3$ is the name of the other player\n\ngosub1610 prints the mg$ value on the screen\n\ngosub2790 is the routine to read a key pressed on the keyboard - use by goto360 to start the routine\n\nwhat is d2$?\nwhat does the gosub1650 subroutine do which is called from line 1630?\n\nCan anyone follow the POKES and PEEKS?\n\nIs it possible to strip this game down to where each person chooses a number and takes turns trying to guess the other player''s number instead of choosing a word, and picking letters.\n\nThat would make the code much easier to follow.\n\nIs it possible to MODIFY the game code and RESAVE it somehow to create a MODIFIED/NEW game which can be added to the Q-Link disk using the ADDGAME program?\n\nIf someone know how to do this and what you need to do it, such as 64copy, please share the black art of Q-Link BASIC game programming with the rest of us so we can understand what is happening in the background.\n\nIf this IS possible, can someone post an article after they create a HELLO WORLDish test game as a skeleton program for using to develop new games?\n\n0-62570 are the lines used for Hangman. Is there a limit to the size of the game which may be created?\n\nHow do you save a program to load at $4B01 if the save"prg",8 saves it and relocates it to $081 instead?\n\nHas anyone tried to do anything like this who has had any success?\n\n  -- MM\n ');
INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES (67, 477, 457, 409, 'I made a D81 of that disk', 'Ray Day', '2005-09-14 11:57:49', 0, 'SUBJ: I made a D81 of that disk        FROM: Ray Day     09/14/2005 S# 477\nIt has a 40 block CBM file on it that covers track 18. It all so has like a DIR sector at track 18 sector 1.\n\nI can''t remember how I got this CBM file on there. Maybe just typing and using a sector editor I don''t know.\n\nI put the D81 up at:\n\nhttp://mywebpages.comcast.net/raymondday/q-link/Q-Link-SL24.zip\n\nIt all most works in VICE. I can get on and pick a name but then when I get some place it says "Your telephone connection to Q-Link has been broken."\n\nIt does work good in a real 64 and a SwiftLink going at 2400 baud. It''s all set up so you don''t have to pick a modem or phone number. You still have to put in a new name when you log in the 1st time.\n\nThis has the PC or Super Q patch on it too. Super Q is not working on this new Q-Link yet. Don''t load it!\n\nYou can save to this disk with out messing it up. It works real good from what I know.\n\nI can''t remember to good. But I think in Super Q if you did something it would mess up this 1581 disk. I am not sure. It was a long time ago.\n\nPost here if you got this D81 working for you. I would like to know.\n\n-Raymond Day ');
