INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES (69, 479, 0, 409, 'Server changed', 'RaymondD2', '2005-09-15 07:57:15', 0, 'SUBJ: Server changed                   FROM: RaymondD2   09/15/2005 S# 479\nIt worked good. I seen it first in the 8 bit message board. So I tested what would happend if I got on the old one. It came up the first screen and said:\n\n"WELCOME TO Q-LINK, null\n\nThis server is no longer operational. The service has been migrated to IP address 66.135.38.238:5190. Please update your configuration.  The server will not disconnect."\n\nThat worked out good. I thought valadating the disk would mess it up. But I guess a user of "null" don''t mess it up.\n\nI am not sure what type of server this is now. It was working good on Jim''s home computer at his home useing his DSL I think it was on only a 300 Mhz Linux PC.\n\nI guess it''s on a real sever now with fast Internet upload and download speeds.\n\nNice Job in the switch Jim!\n\n-Raymond Day ');
