INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES (92, 505, 492, 409, 'BBServer/+.callserver', 'The Icon', '2005-09-21 01:51:06', 0, 'SUBJ: BBServer/+.callserver            FROM: The Icon    09/21/2005 S# 505\nI have made some progress with this project.  I wrote a small program for IMAGE 1.2A BBS called +.callserver which connects, sends text, and disconnects from the BBServer I wrote in java.  However, there are a few issues I am having though.\n\nFirst, I am not able to turn on ASCII translation, and caps appear as graphic symbols on the server.  Lowercase appears as uppercase.  Not sure how to fix this.  I tried...\n\n&,52,16,1   &,52,16,2 ... &,52,16,3\n&,4:a$=chr$(peek(780)and127):ifa$=chr$(13):goto100:goto <same line>\n\nand &,49: etc etc...\n\nUsing these commands from the term program code +.t\n\nSecond, I am not able to read/display the text received by the modem.\n\nI might try to use get#121,an$ but I doubt it is that simple.\n\nM E T A L  M A G E\n ');
