INSERT INTO `messages` VALUES (108, 521, 0, 409, 'QADMIN Panel 1.0a', 'DHartman', '2005-09-30 13:42:48', 3, 'SUBJ: QADMIN Panel 1.0a                FROM: DHartman    09/30/2005 S# 521\nKeith and Jim brought us the actual Q-Link server for the vintage v4 software.  Now, we have a way to manage content online via the web-driven user interface written in PHP by me.\n\nSo far, both ADD MENU and ADD ARTICLE options work as designed and have been tested.\n\nCommodore Software Showcase\n   Software Support Center\n      check out the menu options here\n\nI posted two test articles, and added menus and submenus under menus.  Everything is working and it is LIVE on Q-Link as soon as soon as the SUBMIT button is clicked!\n\nQ-Link users that hit F7 to select move to another area or F5 to display previous menu options, can hit  F1 to select a menu area and it will reload the menu options available at that menu level... including any new menu options submitted.\n\nI have been working on this content management software for Jim''s creation for the past week!\n\nWhat this means, is that soon, the USERS CAN BUILD Q-LINK with CONTENT... just as Jim built the Q-Link Server from the protocol Keith cracked.\n\nContent is ultimately what makes a real online service.\n\nIt has been a very fun and challenging project for me... and I have had to bug Jim a lot to understand how the server and database work to write it... then we had to port the code over to his server, which was configured differently from mine.  But in the end, all is well...\n\nN-Joy.  This is my contribution to the Q-Link movement.  :)\n\n - Dave Hartman\n   DHartman, The Icon, Metal Mage\n ');
